main event: A spherical, white object approximately 16 feet in diameter was observed by military personnel at 16.19'N 109.29'W in the Pacific Ocean. The object was observed for 1 minute, disappeared in 1 second at an elevation angle of 65 degrees, and caused malfunctions in measuring instruments.
interesting points: The object had no sound or trail and its flight path was straight.
The object was initially observed during astronomical observation of evening stars for navigation purposes.
The weather conditions were good with 2/10 cloud cover and no unusual meteorological or astronomical activity.
No air traffic or interception/identification action was reported in the area.
The sighting was evaluated as possibly being a satellite or satellite debris, but the cause remained unknown.
sighted object: a spherical, white object approximately 16 feet in diameter
